reviewText: Wish it was more in depth. Must say I'm biased as I know one of the actresses. She's better than she let on when I met her in person.
Maybe it would be a good movie if they would make a full length version.  I paid 1.99 just to watch what seemed like a movie trailer.

Don't even pop popcorn, the movie (I use the term loosely) will be over.
Bill in Las Vegas

This was one of the most boring films I have ever seen.  It was extremely short for the subject matter presented, and the acting was amateur at best.  There were too many people and dialogs moving in and out of certain scenes that made it seem like amateur stage acting, something you would have seen on Monty Python's Flying Circus, only The Pythons were actually entertaining.
